Is the sun dimned, that gnats do fly in it? The eagle suffers little birds to sing, And is not careful what they mean thereby;
Knowing that with the shadow of his wings,
He can at pleasure stint their melody; Even so mayst thou the giddy men of Rome. Then cheer thy spirit; for know, thou emperor, I will enchant the old Andronicus,

